# apps/web environment — all optional.
#
# --- Local dev (`npm run dev`) ---
# The Vite /boring proxy forwards to BORING_URL (default http://localhost:8080).
# Run your own boringd (see the repo README) and point at it:
#   BORING_URL=http://localhost:8080
#   BORING_TOKEN=<token-if-you-set-one>
#
# --- Production (set on your Vercel/host project, not here) ---
# The browser talks to boringd directly (the TTY/VNC/agent are WebSockets and
# can't go through a serverless function), so expose your endpoint publicly:
#   PUBLIC_BORING_URL=https://your-boringd.example.com
#
# Optional: auto-open an SSH tunnel to a remote/private boringd when you run
# `npm run dev`. Set BORING_TUNNEL to an SSH host; the launcher forwards the port
# from BORING_URL to that host's boringd (localhost:8080), and closes it on exit.
#   BORING_URL=http://localhost:18099
#   BORING_TUNNEL=user@your-box        # or an ~/.ssh/config alias
